\033[1;34m## Common Linux Commands\033[0m

Here is a list of common and universal Linux commands that are essential for managing and interacting with the system:

1. \033[1m\033[94mls\033[0m: List files and directories in the current directory.
2. \033[1m\033[94mpwd\033[0m: Print the current working directory.
3. \033[1m\033[94mcd\033[0m: Change the current directory.
4. \033[1m\033[94mtouch\033[0m: Create an empty file.
5. \033[1m\033[94mmkdir\033[0m: Create a new directory.
6. \033[1m\033[94mrm\033[0m: Remove files or directories.
7. \033[1m\033[94mcp\033[0m: Copy files and directories.
8. \033[1m\033[94mmv\033[0m: Move or rename files and directories.
9. \033[1m\033[94mcat\033[0m: Concatenate and display file content.
10. \033[1m\033[94mless\033[0m or \033[1m\033[94mmore\033[0m: View file content one screen at a time.
11. \033[1m\033[94mhead\033[0m and \033[1m\033[94mtail\033[0m: Display the beginning or end of a file.
12. \033[1m\033[94mgrep\033[0m: Search for text in files using regular expressions.
13. \033[1m\033[94mfind\033[0m: Search for files and directories.
14. \033[1m\033[94mps\033[0m: List running processes.
15. \033[1m\033[94mkill\033[0m: Terminate processes.
16. \033[1m\033[94mtop\033[0m or \033[1m\033[94mhtop\033[0m: Monitor system processes and resource usage.
17. \033[1m\033[94mdf\033[0m: Display disk space usage.
18. \033[1m\033[94mdu\033[0m: Estimate file and directory space usage.
19. \033[1m\033[94mfree\033[0m: Show system memory usage.
20. \033[1m\033[94mtar\033[0m: Create and extract compressed archive files.
21. \033[1m\033[94mchmod\033[0m: Change file permissions.
22. \033[1m\033[94mchown\033[0m: Change file ownership.
23. \033[1m\033[94msudo\033[0m: Execute commands with superuser privileges.
24. \033[1m\033[94mman\033[0m: Display manual pages for commands.
25. \033[1m\033[94mhistory\033[0m: View command history.
26. \033[1m\033[94mdate\033[0m: Show the current date and time.
27. \033[1m\033[94muname\033[0m: Display system information.
28. \033[1m\033[94mifconfig\033[0m or \033[1m\033[94mip\033[0m: View and configure network interfaces.
29. \033[1m\033[94mping\033[0m: Test network connectivity.
30. \033[1m\033[94mssh\033[0m: Securely access remote systems.
31. \033[1m\033[94mscp\033[0m: Securely copy files between systems.
32. \033[1m\033[94mwget\033[0m or \033[1m\033[94mcurl\033[0m: Download files from the internet.
33. \033[1m\033[94mnc\033[0m: Network utility for reading from and writing to network connections.

These commands cover a wide range of system administration and everyday tasks and are available on most Linux distributions. You can use the \033[1m\033[94mman\033[0m command followed by the command name to access the manual pages for more information about each command and its options.
